headline: Adobe Impresses the Market With Strong Free Cash Flow - Is ADBE Stock Worth Buying?
summary: Adobe Inc.'s fiscal Q4 revenue was up 10% YoY and +11% YoY for the FY. Moreover, its free cash flow (FCF) margins were over 41.45%. That implies ADBE stock could be worth over 21% more over the next year.

headline: Adobe delivered ‘clean’ Q4 beat, says RBC Capital
summary: RBC Capital keeps an Outperform rating and $430 price target on Adobe (ADBE) after its Q4 results. The company minimized the noise while delivering a clean beat to end the year as its management continues to build the narrative around its role as a the central orchestration layer for digital assets, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
